Description:
Picture Perfect - Space, Quality & Style
Be amazed by this impeccably presented and impressive home nestled in a quiet court. This picture perfect renovated home would be ideal for a first home buyer, investor or family home buyer looking for stylish low maintenance living or a savvy investment.
As you enter you are greeted by the fresh white paint creating a lovely contemporary feel throughout.
The free flowing floorplan offers three bedrooms with built in robes; master includes, ensuite, walk in robe, ceiling fan and modern pendant lights.
The modern bathroom is dressed by quality fittings coupled with an impressive colour palette, presented beautifully including bath, shower and a separate main toilet. The large living space flows through to the open dining and kitchen area. The kitchen accommodates a dishwasher and a substantial
cupboard storage and breakfast bar. The home also features ducted heating and split system cooling for your all year round weather needs.
The backyard boosts a fantastic undercover entertaining area that seamlessly combines with the manicured and well maintained backyard and offers great storage with a large garden shed.
Set on approximately 799 m2 this property generously ticks all the boxes.
This property is priced to sell, exceptional value. Enquire today!
Home Owner: “I love that it's located in such a quiet court, filled with great neighbours.”
Roncon Real Estate - An Agency like no other!
All stated dimensions and areas are approximate. Particulars herein are for information only and do not constitute representation by the Owner or Agent.

Description:
Original Character Home, Perfect for a Revamp!
Be inspired by this neat character weatherboard home, nestled amongst cottage gardens. Located in the popular blue chip part of the Whittington area, only a short commute to the Surf Coast and Geelong CBD location suits all. Situated on a large 596m2 block (approx.), with much yard space at rear. Upon entry you are greeted with three oversize bedrooms, master with built in robes. A central family bathroom with original charm, features bath over shower. The large country kitchen packed with warmth and appeal offers plenty of bench space. Living areas are to the rear of the home and overlooks the large grassed area.
The possibilities within this structurally sound home are endless, with this property awaiting a revamp! The yard is substantially unique, equipped with oversized single lock up garage or tradesman's haven, undercover car parking and stable boundaries which boasts privacy. The backyard highlights growth with copious of room to move, making it ideal for possible re-development, a granny flat, or a perfect haven for the tradesman (STCA). So, investors, re-developers or the overall handy man, please take note of this property. With endless of capital growth, add this character home to your property portfolio. Inspect ASAP!

Description:
A Unique & Rare Surprise Surrounded by Immaculate Gardens
Walk through a cream picket fence into an immaculate cottage garden which leads you to the facade of the home. This brick home is beautifully kept and on entry you are welcomed by the living area with split system heating and cooling additionally set with gas heating. The hallway entrance flows to dining or second living area which oversees the kitchen. The newly updated kitchen is set with gas cooking and electric oven appliances, which has an overlooking breakfast bar with views of the backyard. To the facade to the home, is the sleeping quarters with three roomy bedrooms with built in robes linking with the bathroom. Bathroom features bath, shower and leads to toilet and large laundry area. The yard of this home is substantially large and is nestled with cottage gardens and lush lawn. Attached to the home is a single carport area or entertainment area.
Location is convenient for all; close schools and only a short 10 minute walk to Newcomb Central and a small drive to Geelong CBD.
A current rental return of $250.00 per week is implemented with a lease signed will early August 2014. This home is one not to be missed, investors please take note and first home buyers this could be the home you have been looking for. Enquire today.

Description:
A top opportunity to invest!
Nestled in a quiet court this 3BR property serves as a comfortable family home to own or invest. Situated close to schools, major shopping centres and easy access to Bellarine Peninsula, the property is well maintained on a generous 632sqm secure and private block with established gardens. The home is tastefully presented having recently undergone a fresh update with new carpets and painted throughout. A spacious living room off the entry has gas heating & wood fire and ceiling fan, and is positioned next to the galley kitchen and meals area. This bright casual area opens onto an expansive pergola, fernery and very neat yard. The practical kitchen has loads of storage space and bench tops, and adjoins the hallway leading to three bedrooms, laundry and family-sized bathroom. Ample parking is provided with a driveway and double garage at the rear. The property is an ideal first home or investment with lots of appeal that will tempt you today!

Description:
Stylish & Fully Renovated

A timber front deck leads one to a separate family lounge area overseeing yard and an undercover alfresco area. Polished timber floor boards follow you through to the kitchen. Beautifully updated the kitchen features stainless steel appliances, freestanding oven with canopy, dishwasher and much bench space and storage choices overseeing dining and rear access to the external yard.
All the bedrooms have polished boards, built in robes and ceiling fans for cooling. Master includes, en-suite with semi frame less glass doors, modern square floating basin and toilet. Family bathroom nestled between bedrooms, is tiled and presented beautifully including bath and shower. Gas ducted heating and cooling is throughout the home. To the far corner of this large block is a double lockup garage, and a single carport to the side of the home.
On such a large block, the opportunities are endless, with room to extend or redevelop STCA this property is full of potential. This property is priced to sell, exceptional value. Enquire today!

Description:
EXCEED YOUR EXPECTATIONS
A fantastic investment, first home or downsizer awaits the successful purchaser. Nestled safely on a block of 11 well-maintained and presented units you will find our little gem.
This 2 bedroom unit is not short on space both inside and out! You can look forward to a large light filled living area, kitchen which overlooks the living area with gas stove top and ample cupboards, with plenty of room for a dining table to the side. 2 decent sized bedrooms with BIR's, bathroom with bath and shower, good sized laundry with access to the yard. The outdoors area is broken into 2 parts grassed and paved; as you enter the property you will be greeted with a wide stretch of grass that veers right around the property and ends where your paved BBQ area begins, all surrounded by a tidy garden and enough room for a small veggie patch or herb garden.
This unit is as neat as a pin and equipped with extras such as heating, cooling SLUB and separate toilet, located in a complex that is well maintained with great street appeal and offers a great level of privacy. Located moments from Buckley's Entertainment Centre, White Eagle House, Saint Albans Reserve , Barwon Valley Golf Club and only a 10 minute drive to Belmont shopping precinct and Barwon River.
Inspect today to have all your expectations exceeded!

Description:
Surprise! A home with size
Room to move is certainly promised at this huge 33sm 4BR residence. Home living couldn't be easier with a generous, flexible open floor plan and comfortable, light-filled rooms. The brick residence is a fabulous find, offering close proximity to schools and shopping centres. From the street, you wouldn't expect the front door to lead to an expansive living area boasting an exclusive bar, casual lounge and meals area, formal dining and a separate lounge room on a lower level. Brick and timber features are noticeable throughout, and a wood fire creates added warmth to the home which has ducted
heating and split system heating and cooling. The easy flow of the living area means entertaining is simple, especially with the fully equipped kitchen offering plenty of space to prepare meals before mingling around the adjacent bar. At the rear of the home is the laundry, main bathroom with spa, and four big bedrooms including main with walk-in robe and en-suite. If a home with size is what you're looking for, this fabulous home set on a large beautifully landscaped 677m2 block will be hard to surpass.

Description:
Picture perfect family home
When it comes to finding the complete family home, it's easy to see why this property fits the bill. Only 12 months old, the spacious 3BR home presents a contemporary design and easy lifestyle in a quiet family friendly neighbourhood. Not far from St Albans Park, schools, public transport and Newcomb and Bellarine shopping centres. This stunning home offers a low maintenance lifestyle and options for indoor and outdoor entertaining.
